CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 29, 1959, pg. 5 reads: "Off to Detroit and Canada - The Centre Ave. Branch YMCA boys are shown as they waited to enter the bus for their trip to Detroit, Mich., and Windsor, Canada, Aug. 21. Parents gathered for that last-minute farewell to their sons.  Paul M. Dykes, youth secretary, and Lou Davenport, a member of the youth committee, accompanied the boys.  Many interesting spots were visited on the 24-hour trip, which included a sightseeing tour of Canada, outing at Belle Isle, swimming at the St. Antoine Branch YMCA, and meals.  This as an annual bus-trip activity, sponsored for members of the Summer Fun Club.  A different city of interest is selected each summer. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of Centre Avenue Branch YMCA boys boarding bus for trip to Detroit, Michigan and Windsor, Canada
